<paragraph blockId="1.[151,677,223,285]" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,265,259,285]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionStartId-2="4.[151,250,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox-0="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetBox-2="[167,1429,237,1496]" captionTargetId-0="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetId-1="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetId-2="figure-48@4.[159,1429,237,1504]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (female paratype). A. Terminalia, ventral view. B. Cleared pregential plate, ventral view. C. Cleared vagina, dorsal view. D. Cleared vagina, lateral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899853" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6899853/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Adult habitus</emphasis>
. Head brown to dark brown; antennae, mouthparts and palpi lighter than head; compound eyes black. Pronotum brown to dark brown, rectangular, anterior corners obtuse and posterior ones nearly right-angled. Legs generally brownish but femora darker; wing membranes pale to brownish with darker veins. Abdominal segments brown with paler hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,475,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[278,389,475,501]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox-0="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId-0="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetId-1="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 6.0 mm (n=3), hindwing length 5.0 mm. Tergum 9 sclerotized, anterior margin with a wide, shallow medial incision, posterior margin without spines or long hairs. Sternum 9 (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1430,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,180,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">2b</figureCitation>
) with oval-shaped vesicle, length ca. 1.3X maximum width, lacks clothing hairs; hypoproct basally broad and rectangular, gradually tapering towards short, triangular apex. Tergum 10 (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1094,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1108,1136,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">2a</figureCitation>
) darkly sclerotized except the narrow, longitudinal, medial concavity beneath epiproct; anterolateral part of the concavity bears many tiny black spines. Cercus long and distinctly sclerotized except for inner portion and center of apex, generally parallelsided posterior to wider base and before enlarged apex, erect in lateral view. Apex with a strong ventrolateral hook pointing caudally, and a rounded intralateral bulb; vestigial second segment located on distal extreme of cercal head, surrounded by an open membranous ring (
<figureCitation box="[691,810,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1a–e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[821,878,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">2a–c</figureCitation>
). Epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1150,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,181,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[213,1374,181,1874]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (male, a–e: paratype; f: holotype). A. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. B. Cleared terminalia, ventral view. C. Cleared terminalia, showing cerci and epiproct in dorsocaudal view. D. Cerci and paraproct before NaOH treatment, ventrocaudal view. E. Cleared terminalia, showing oblique lateral view of cerci and epiproct. F. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899847/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 1a, c, f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1161,1246,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">2a, d–e</figureCitation>
): subrectangular, with widened apical half and abruptly narrowed, triangular apex; nearly 2X longer than maximum width. Ventral sclerite heavily sclerotized, forming large lateral knobs at basolateral corners, with 7–8 ventral spines on the narrow parallel ridges; the ridges are distinctly diverging towards the apical sclerites. Arms of ventral sclerite forming an incomplete, relatively short and thin ring in dorsal view. Apical sclerites large, extend along apicolateral margin of the epiproct and joined with apical lobes of the ring, bearing 2–4 stout lateral spines. Heavily sclerotized lateral arms slender and short, extend along lower surface of elevated medial hump (
<figureCitation box="[964,1075,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Fig. 2c–d</figureCitation>
). Paraproct (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1302,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1638,1662]" captionTargetBox="[167,1402,289,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[158,1430,273,1615]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (holotype male). A. Terminalia, dorsal, view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Terminalia, lateral view. D. Cleared epiproct, dorsal view. E. Cleared epiproct, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
): outer lobe short and subquadrate, outer margin strongly sclerotized, apex narrower and slightly bilobed but the recessed edge is obscure in 
<specimenCount box="[301,450,1052,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
; inner lobe short and well sclerotized, narrow at base and then slightly swollen towards obtusely triangular apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1123,1149]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[300,367,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[167,1429,237,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[159,1429,237,1504]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (female paratype). A. Terminalia, ventral view. B. Cleared pregential plate, ventral view. C. Cleared vagina, dorsal view. D. Cleared vagina, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899853/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[575,659,1123,1150]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
(n=1), hindwing length 
<quantity box="[926,1013,1123,1150]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
. Pregenital plate trapezoidal, its apical width is one third the width and over half the length of sternum 8. Posterior margin nearly truncate, the overhanging part dark brown. A pair of lateral brown markings present on sternum 8 (
<figureCitation box="[996,1119,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[167,1429,237,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[159,1429,237,1504]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (female paratype). A. Terminalia, ventral view. B. Cleared pregential plate, ventral view. C. Cleared vagina, dorsal view. D. Cleared vagina, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899853/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 3a–b</figureCitation>
), but poorly delimited after being cleared. Sternum 9 moderately sclerotized, anterior edge nearly straight. Vaginal complex (
<figureCitation box="[1250,1370,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[167,1429,237,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[159,1429,237,1504]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. (female paratype). A. Terminalia, ventral view. B. Cleared pregential plate, ventral view. C. Cleared vagina, dorsal view. D. Cleared vagina, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899853/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 3c–d</figureCitation>
) with membranous spermatheca bearing two wrinkled lateral pockets; medially depressed and posteriorly divergent with two slender bifurcations.
</paragraph>
