<subSubSection box="[199,1431,1519,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" box="[199,1431,1519,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Etymology</emphasis>
. The epithet refers to Mr. Jixiang Wang, who guided us to these far and hardly accessible villages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[514,634,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Figs. 4a–b</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[658,725,1555,1581]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[741,947,1555,1581]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Qinghai Province</collectingRegion>
). The types are known only from two sites of the Qilian Mountain National Park. They were collected in headwater of two small creeks with stony substrate over 
<quantity box="[209,295,1627,1654]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" unit="m" value="3000.0">3000 m</quantity>
above sea level, and 
<specimenCount box="[539,641,1627,1654]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[649,745,1628,1654]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">paratype</typeStatus>
was caught by sweeping the alpine meadows near a creek in Deqian Village.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="488" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,2014]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="488" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Remarks</emphasis>
. On the basis of the epiproct’s large apical sclerite and lobed ring, and the strong apical hook of the cerci, the new species seems to be related to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martynov" authorityYear="1928" box="[701,943,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[701,943,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Nemoura brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Muranyi, D." box="[1094,1276,1735,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref3845" refString="Muranyi, D. (2007) New and little-known stoneflies (Plecoptera) from Albania and the neighbouring countries. Zootaxa, 1533 (1), 1 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1533.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Murányi (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. This group is the most diverse in the Caucasus and 
<collectingCountry box="[584,683,1771,1797]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, and the epiproct of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Ma &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[922,1103,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jixiangwangi">
<emphasis box="[922,1103,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. jixiangwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhiltzova 1967" authorityName="Zhiltzova" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taurica">
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. taurica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[151,326,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="850 - 856" refId="ref4907" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. (1967) New Genus and three new species of Stone-flies (Plecoptera) from Caucasus and Crimea. Revue d' Entomologie de l'URSS, 46 (4), 850 - 856." type="journal article" year="1967">Zhiltzova 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, known from 
<collectingCountry box="[488,570,1807,1833]" name="Greece" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Greece</collectingCountry>
, Crimea and 
<collectingCountry box="[723,805,1807,1833]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Ma &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[817,997,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jixiangwangi">
<emphasis box="[817,997,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. jixiangwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from that species by larger lateral arm of the epiproct and more robust cercus. The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Ma &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[960,1140,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jixiangwangi">
<emphasis box="[960,1140,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. jixiangwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also reminiscent of the Central Asian 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhiltzova, 1976" authorityName="Zhiltzova" authorityYear="1976" box="[312,602,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alaica">
<emphasis box="[312,415,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. alaica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[422,602,1879,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="1476 - 1481" refId="ref4947" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. (1976) Dopolneniya k faune vesnyanok semeystva Nemouridae (Insecta, Plecoptera) Sredney Azii. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 56 (10), 1476 - 1481." type="journal article" year="1976">Zhiltzova, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in the shape of paraproct and cercus, but differs in the epiproct and the apex of the cercus. Some Far East species like 
<taxonomicName authority="Muranyi, 2011" authorityName="Muranyi" authorityYear="2011" box="[790,1074,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquila">
<emphasis box="[790,898,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. aquila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Muranyi, D. &amp; Park, S. J." box="[907,1074,1915,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="70 - 85" refId="ref3889" refString="Muranyi, D. &amp; Park, S. J. (2011) Contribution to the fall stonefly (Plecoptera) fauna of Korea. Illiesia 7 (06), 70 - 85. [http: // www 2. pms-lj. si / illiesia / Illiesia 07 - 06. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2011">Murányi, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in: 
<bibRefCitation author="Muranyi, D. &amp; Park, S. J." box="[1132,1389,1915,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="70 - 85" refId="ref3889" refString="Muranyi, D. &amp; Park, S. J. (2011) Contribution to the fall stonefly (Plecoptera) fauna of Korea. Illiesia 7 (06), 70 - 85. [http: // www 2. pms-lj. si / illiesia / Illiesia 07 - 06. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2011">Murányi &amp; Park 2011</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Zwick, 2010" authorityName="Zwick" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. rugosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[237,382,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="75 - 97" refId="ref5042" refString="Zwick, P. (2010) New species and new records of Plecoptera from Korea and the Russian Far East. Illiesia, 6 (9), 75 - 97. [http: // www 2. pms-lj. si / illiesia / Illiesia 06 - 09. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2010">Zwick, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Teslenko, 2018" authorityName="Teslenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[393,694,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sirotskii">
<emphasis box="[393,515,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. sirotskii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Boumans, L." box="[523,694,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="153 - 164" refId="ref4184" refString="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Boumans, L. (2018) A new species of Nemoura Latreille (Plecoptera: Nemouridae) from Amur River Basin (South of the Russian Far East). Zootaxa, 4472 (1), 153 - 164. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4472.1.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Teslenko, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in: 
<bibRefCitation author="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Boumans, L." box="[748,1057,1951,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="153 - 164" refId="ref4184" refString="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Boumans, L. (2018) A new species of Nemoura Latreille (Plecoptera: Nemouridae) from Amur River Basin (South of the Russian Far East). Zootaxa, 4472 (1), 153 - 164. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4472.1.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Teslenko &amp; Boumans 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zwick, 2010" authorityName="Zwick" authorityYear="2010" box="[1120,1394,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripotini">
<emphasis box="[1120,1245,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">N. tripotini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[1252,1394,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" pagination="75 - 97" refId="ref5042" refString="Zwick, P. (2010) New species and new records of Plecoptera from Korea and the Russian Far East. Illiesia, 6 (9), 75 - 97. [http: // www 2. pms-lj. si / illiesia / Illiesia 06 - 09. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2010">Zwick, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are superficially similar to the new species, but all differ with much narrow apical sclerite and ring lobe complex of the epiproct. There is no known Chinese species that can be closely related. The trapezoidal female pregenital plate of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Ma &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,329,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jixiangwangi">
<emphasis box="[151,329,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">N. jixiangwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of the females of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martynov" authorityYear="1928" box="[763,893,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[763,893,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but its characters do not allow distinction at the specific level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
